  "text": "SephoraWhile each product featured is independently selected by our editors, we may include paid promotion. If you buy something through our links, we may earn commission. Read more about our Product Review Guidelines here.Memorial Day deals are in full swing, with everything from mattresses and furniture to workout must haves and all things fashion on sale. Although the holiday weekend pretty much kicks off the summer, it's also the best time to score amazing deals on all your favorite beauty products. You can stock up on hair-care products, skin-care picks, summer makeup, and more. Sephora is one of the best destinations to score amazing Memorial Day beauty deals, with up to 50 percent off through May 26, and the retailer has more than 1,000 products on sale this year. We made your life easier and narrowed it down to the top 26 picks from top brands like Color Wow, Farmacy, and Clinique. Dealing with acne and oily skin? Stock up on a clay mask infused with aloe vera from Peter Thomas Roth. Hydrate your hair with a luxe hair treatment that will help diminish dullness and dryness. We also found a few deals on acne treatments and exfoliating serums that promise to deliver a glowy complexion. Get ready for summer with deals on makeup removers, hydrating moisturizers, and quality sunscreens. We all love a good deal on our favorite beauty products, so shop our top picks ahead.sephora.comBest Sunscreen on SaleFarmacy Green Defense Daily Mineral Sunscreen SPF 30 ($28, originally $37) Farmacy's Green Defense Daily Mineral Sunscreen SPF 30 is an editor-backed pick that leaves a beautiful glow on the skin. It is a fast-absorbing, lightweight product that is reef safe and free of silicones and fragrance. It doesn't leave a white cast, either.sephora.comBest Hydrating Moisturizer on SaleBelif The True Cream Aqua Bomb ($29, originally $38) If your skin leans dry, there's no better time to stock up on the Belif The True Cream Moisturizing Bomb. It has a whipped, lightweight gel-cream texture that feels deeply hydrating on the skin. It's great for all skin types, including sensitive skin.sephora.comBest Cleansing Balm Makeup Remover on SaleClinique Take The Day Off Cleansing Balm Makeup Remover ($33, originally $44) Clinique's Take The Day Off Cleansing Balm Makeup Remover removes even the most powerful makeup without leaving behind any residue. A little dollop goes a long way in breaking down waterproof mascara and full-coverage foundation. It transforms from a balm to an oil as it dissolves makeup. Just splash a little bit of water to emulsify the solution to take the day off.sephora.comBest Hair Mask For Dry Hair on SaleColor Wow Money Mask Deep Hydrating \u0026 Strengthening Hair Treatment ($34, originally $45) Revive dry hair with Color Wow's Money Mask, which is an intensely hydrating treatment that helps detangle and soften the hair. This weekly hair treatment is great for all hair types and textures, and promises to help reduce frizz as well. Your hair will look and feel shinier, softer, and become more manageable.sephora.comBest Clay Mask on SalePeter Thomas Roth Goodbye Acne™ Therapeutic Sulfur Mask ($36, originally $52) From dealing with pores to preventing breakouts, Peter Thomas Roth's Goodbye Acne™ Therapeutic Sulfur Mask is perfect for those with oily skin. It uses Kaolin and Bentonite Clays with aloe to minimize the look of pores and draw out dirt, toxins, and excess oil. It's gentle and calming while it visibly smooths and refines skin texture.sephora.comBest Exfoliating Serum on SaleHoney Glow 17% AHA + BHA Resurfacing Acid Serum ($45, originally $60) Farmacy's Honeymoon Glow AHA Resurfacing Night Serum has a potent blend of AHAs and BHAs to help smooth out the skin's texture and tone. Whether you're dealing with breakouts, fine lines, or dark spots, incorporating this night serum into your routine will boost your skin's progress. Plus, it's got hyaluronic acid and honey to help soothe and calm the skin while infusing it with hydration.sephora.comBest Eyeshadow Palette on SaleMakeup By Mario Ethereal Eyes Eyeshadow Palette: Moonlight ($49, originally $68) From everyday looks to something glamorous and romantic, Makeup By Mario Ethereal Eyes Eyeshadow Palette is a staple eyeshadow palette and a fan favorite. The palette has an array of mattes and shimmers that include warm-toned neutrals, and golds. Each shadow is pigmented, so a little goes a long way. The shadows are blendable as well for a seamless look.sephora.comBest Blow-Dryer Brush on SaleMoroccanoil 4-in-1 Blow-Dryer Brush ($90, originally $120) Moroccanoil's 4-in-1 Blow-Dryer Brush is designed for all hair types, and features advanced ionic technology to reduce drying time and minimize static, as well as far-infrared light to gently heat strands from the inside out to reduce thermal exposure and lock in moisture.- Additional reporting by Balim TezelAnvita Reddy (she/her) is a former assistant editor for PS Shopping. She has a passion for products and reviews home gadgets, cookware, tech, and more. Having dealt with acne as a teenager and into adulthood, her expertise lies in beauty. At PS, she tested skin care, makeup, and hair care, plus countless other beauty products.Balim Tezel (she/her) is a shopping updates editor at PS and the founder of Maison des Nus, a New York-based affordable luxury brand. She graduated from Northwestern University's Medill School of Journalism.",
